        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks Horner for his letter [about <hi rend="italic">Volcanic islands</hi>].</p>  
<p>Discusses craters of elevation with respect to the views of Leopold von Buch and Élie de Beaumont. Compares Lyell’s views to those of continental geologists. Mentions reading A. D. d’Orbigny [<hi rend="italic">Voyage dans l’Amérique méridionale</hi> (1835–47)].</p> 
            <p>Encloses note from Emma to Mrs Horner, inviting the Horners to visit Down.</p>
        </abstract>
